main event: A 13-year-old boy spotted a round, blue-white object with red lights over Portsmouth, New Hampshire on March 23, 1966.
interesting points: The object traveled at an estimated speed of 300-400 miles per hour.
The object emitted a humming sound.
The object was brighter than a full moon and was seen about 2,500 feet above the ground.
The object changed color from blue-white to red.
Other witnesses besides the 13-year-old boy saw the object.
sighted object: a round, blue-white object with red lights
witnesses: a 13-year-old boy and other unspecified witnesses
